OL,3,CLegionella bacteria found in showers
OL,4,Cof public pool
OL,6,FJersey's government has clarified that
OL,7,Fthe detected bacteria is not the type
OL,8,Fthat causes more than 90% of
OL,9,FLegionnaires' disease cases, although
OL,10,Fit can cause sickness.
OL,12,FIt added there is "no risk" from other
OL,13,Fwater sources such as the sinks, water
OL,14,Ffountains and the pool itself which
OL,15,Fall remain open, along with the
OL,16,Fcentre's changing rooms.
OL,18,FLegionella was first named in the
OL,19,F1970s, with more than 50 recognised
OL,20,Fspecies - only half are harmful to
OL,21,Fhumans.
